[{'comment_id': 933256822, 'comment_body': 'min_p should maybe be a parameter to this model instead of hardcoded ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 29, 13, 20, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934681681, 'comment_body': "More descriptive names would be useful for extensions/alternative uses. In the past, we've used `_fast` to refer to numba-fied methods that do the same as their reference methods, but here, both are using `numba.jit`.  ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 15, 53, 43, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934698997, 'comment_body': 'is this "thickening" the grid of the distribution of cash-on-hand? what is particular about this construction that is different from `make_grid_exp_mult`? If this is doing something that can't be accomplished by `make_grid_exp_mult` maybe it should be its own utility method.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 16, 12, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934702595, 'comment_body': 'So this condition is (cycles == 1 and T_cycle !=0)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 16, 16, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934705369, 'comment_body': 'is `T_cycle < 1` ever?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 16, 20, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934706331, 'comment_body': 'This could be 
`if (self.cycles == 0) or (self.cycles == 1 and self.T_cycle !=0):`
to avoid code repetition I think ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 16, 21, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934708022, 'comment_body': 'Is this a probability distribution? Would it be useful to use our `DiscreteDistribution` constructor here?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 16, 23, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934709150, 'comment_body': "Is there a model that has cycles==1 and T_cycle==0? I'm thinking this should never happen, and if it does, it's probably a bug. ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 16, 24, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'alanlujan91', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934953659, 'comment_body': 'yes this condition is meant as  (cycles == 1 and T_cycle !=0). 

T_cycle is never less than 1 I believe', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 22, 4, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934955583, 'comment_body': "This is a function that takes in a grid, a set of values that may lie between the gridpoints, and finally the associated probabilities of each the values and returns the probability mass of each gridpoint. I don't think itd be useful to use DiscreteDistribution here", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 22, 7, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934956003, 'comment_body': "I'm not sure, that is why I was so specific on the conditional cases.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 22, 7, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934956328, 'comment_body': 'Agreed, good catch.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 22, 8, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934956923, 'comment_body': "It does thicken if that means to increase the density. Chris had asked me to do this a while back but I'm not sure whethe rmake_grid_exp_mult can thicken, I feel as though it just concentrates points near the bottom end.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 22, 9, 46, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934957039, 'comment_body': 'Ok got it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 22, 9, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 938551151, 'comment_body': 'The T_cycle !=0 problem is exclusive of the cycles=0 problem so it is not unfortunately.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 5, 7, 57, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'wdu9', 'type': 'User'}]
